Chcem vediet

Cloning and testing the project. You don't need any real webserver, db server, nor mail server
while testing. They are simulated by the testing environment.

 1. Dependencies on system packages:
     -- python (ver. 2.7.x)
     -- python-virtualenv
     -- git

 2. Prepare your environment and clone the project:
        $ cd project_dir
        $ virtualenv env
        $ ./env/bin/pip install Django
        $ mkdir chcemvediet
        git...
        $ cd chcemvediet
        $ ../env/bin/python manage.py syncdb --noinput

 3. Run testing webserver:
        $ cd project_dir/chcemvediet
        $ ../env/bin/python manage.py runserver
    Run testing mailserver in another shell (it will dump all incoming emails to stdout):
        $ cd project_dir/chcemvediet
        $ ../env/bin/python -m smtpd -n -c DebuggingServer localhost:1025
    And navigate your browser to:
        http://127.0.0.1:8000/

User registration module is not finished, yet. To login a test user use 'kalerab'/'kalerab' for
login/password.

Please make sure you won't push any autogenerated files to the git repository, such as your local
database.db or *.pyc files.


